## USER RESEARCH

**Where the audience talks (non-Reddit sources):**
Quora nail threads, TikTok comment sections on salon content (Nail Career Education, QT Nails & Lashes), Ask MetaFilter beauty threads, Coveteur reader comments, salon-specific blog comments, YouTube "first time nails" tutorial comments, Lemon8 nail journeys.

### Top 5 Pain Points (Sourced from Forum + TikTok + Quora)

1. **Got oval instead of almond** — "I said almond, she filed it round and I didn't know how to correct her mid-appointment." The almond/oval boundary is blurry in execution even when the client knows the name. Extremely common first-timer complaint across TikTok discover pages (24.5M oval vs almond posts) and Quora threads.

2. **Don't know what words to use** — "I'm scared of the nail tech." The terminology barrier (gel vs acrylic vs BIAB vs overlay, tip vs form, taper vs point) stops people from knowing if they're asking for the right thing. Quora thread: "My first nail salon experience was confusing and nothing was explained." MetaFilter: "I'm overwhelmed by the amount of information." Widely reported anxiety, especially first-timers.

3. **Confused about whether they need extensions** — "Do I need fake nails to get almond shape?" Most first-timers do not understand the distinction between overlays (on natural nail), tips/extensions (added length), and the Gel X / sculpted options. They assume almond nails = fake nails and vice versa.

4. **Don't know the shape sub-types exist** — Audiences on TikTok are discovering that "narrow almond" is a real instruction. Viral QT Nails TikTok: "Say narrow almond — saying narrow does make a difference." Many clients ask for almond but do not specify width and receive a wider, rounder version. The sub-types (narrow, soft, standard) are not surfaced in any current top-ranking post.

5. **Can't speak up mid-appointment when it goes wrong** — "I left and hated them but paid and said nothing." Coveteur editorial + Quora: clients are emotionally stuck when the shape is going wrong; they don't know how or when to intervene politely. The window to fix shape closes quickly once filing begins.

**User Sentiment:** Anxious and under-informed — wants to feel prepared before the appointment, not educated afterwards.

