**Structure Reasoning:** The H2s are ordered to map the reader's journey: realisation of the problem → pre-appointment decisions → in-chair language → active monitoring → recovery. Each H2 is a real query the reader has in that moment. Sections 1–3 handle the pre-appointment confusion; sections 4–6 are pre-appointment preparation; sections 7–9 are in-chair and post-appointment. The post links naturally to gel-vs-acrylic in H2 #4, to do-almond-nails-suit-me in H2 #7, to the pillar in the intro, to almond-nails-aftercare at the close, and to why-almond-nails-keep-breaking in H2 #3 (extension vs natural nail prep failures).

